En images

     * JIMEI x ARLES 2019 International Photo Festival 22.11.2019 —
       05.01.2020 YI LIAN ASK FOR THE...
       JIMEI x ARLES 2019 International Photo Festival 22.11.2019 —
       05.01.2020 YI LIAN ASK FOR THE MOON In 2010, Yi Lian started to
       record his dreams. He repeated the course of these diaristic
       accounts for thousands of days and nights. From the moment he
       transferred his visions into written word, the dreams established
       independent structures and new meanings. photo: Yi Lian, A tale
       told by an idiot, 2019. Image installation, Acrylic UV Printing,20
       x 11 cm. Courtesy of the artist. #rencontresarles #photography
       #photographie #exhibition #exposition #festival #china #xiamen
       @jimei_arles
     * Accrochages en cours à Jimei en Chine... JIMEI x ARLES 2019
       International Photo...
       Accrochages en cours à Jimei en Chine... JIMEI x ARLES 2019
       International Photo Festival 22.11.2019 — 05.01.2020
       #rencontresarles #photography #photographie #exhibition #exposition
       #festival #china #xiamen @jimei_arles photo: @cespei
     * JIMEI x ARLES 2019 International Photo Festival 22.11.2019 —
       05.01.2020 WU DING THE HISTORY OF...
       JIMEI x ARLES 2019 International Photo Festival 22.11.2019 —
       05.01.2020 WU DING THE HISTORY OF CIRCLES From “Real dimensions” to
       “Restricted rhythm”, almost all of Wu Ding’s exhibitions over the
       past six or seven years have tackled a range of philosophical
       concepts in an effort to provoke discussion. The artist has worked
       to ensure these discussions stay at an abstract and pure level.
       photo: Wu Ding, Infinitely approach to an origin point No.3, 2019,
       60 x 40 cm, photograph. Courtesy of the artist. #rencontresarles
       #photography #photographie #exhibition #exposition #festival #china
       #xiamen @jimei_arles
